div1.p: In the District Court of the third Judicial District of Washington Territory of Washington holding thems at Seattle for the Countries of King & Kitsep:
In the matter of the application of C. W. Hutchinson on for Habeas Corpus} Territory of Wahsington County of King ss Order No4704

An now it appearing to me by petition of C.W.Hutchinson that he is illegally restrained of his liberty by one W H Harris Pren in this country of King withouhgt proper authority - now this is to order that the said Lewis now Doren do appear before me as the District Court house of King County in Seattle, where I am holden open the day of November AD 1885 at 2 1/2 O'Clock P.M. and then and there to have and produce the body of the said C.W.Hutchinson that & may inquire of and determine why
the said Hutchingson is so illegally restrained and the Clerk of the said District Court is ordered to issue a writ in accordance with this order,
Ywen this 12th day of November AD 1885
In the Dist, Ct. of the 3 & gudicial Dist of Washington Territory
In re petition of CWHutchinson for Habeas Corpus
FILED NOV 12 1885 James Seavey Clerk By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk
